metadata.name: Wonderscapes #135
metadata.description:
In the infinite abyss of wondering there are some random moments of beauty which will stay in memory and at the end they will remind us that exploration and efforts were not in vain.

This artwork is rendered in real-time using custom webStyleGAN model (~25mb) which was trained on a dataset of about 5000 wonderscapes generated by DALL-E from OpenAI.

In addition to the main generative model, there is a CNN classifier model that filters the rendered images by predicting similarity to landscapes (this may take some time with each generation).

On top of the image generated by the neural network, there is a processing script that converts the value of each pixel into a colored ASCII character, the final result is a 64x64 vector grid with 4096 text symbols.

Controls:
- Press [s] to save the high resolution image

metadata.name: CEV Generator #25
metadata.description:
Closed-eye hallucinations and closed-eye visualizations (CEV) are a distinct class of hallucination (technically a pseudohallucination since there is generally awareness that the perceived experience is not real). These types of hallucinations generally only occur when one's eyes are closed or when one is in a darkened room. They can be a form of phosphene. Some people report closed-eye hallucinations under the influence of psychedelics. (From Wikipedia.)

metadata.name: play/plaque #339
metadata.description:
A grid of trailing shapes. Each shape in the line wants to be like the shape in front of it.

The traits
4 shapes: square, cross, triangle, circle
5 grid sizes 1->5 with 1x1 grids being rarest (5%)
2 fill styles: hollow (80%, crosses can't be hollow) and filled (20%)
20% chance for all shapes to be the same
6 color palettes:
- Coffee and Blueberry
- Tropicana
- Monochrome
- Spectrum
- Peach and Pear
- Goji and Kelp

Made by Sam Tsao (@sam___tsao)
